Claims CLAIMS What is Claimed: 1. A wireless transmit/receive unit (WTRU) comprising: a processor configured to: receive a first radio resource control (RRC) message from a distributed unit (DU) RRC entity, wherein the first RRC message indicates first configuration information and a first interdependency characteristic; in response to receiving the first RRC message, set an interdependence RRC message timer based on an interdependence RRC message reception time duration; receive a second RRC message from a control unit (CU) RRC entity, wherein the second RRC message indicates second configuration information and a second interdependency characteristic; determine that a first condition and a second condition are satisfied, wherein the first condition is determined to be satisfied based on the second RRC message being received before expiry of the interdependence RRC message timer, and wherein the second condition is determined to be satisfied based on the first interdependency characteristic and the second interdependency characteristic; and update, based on the determination that the first condition and the second condition are satisfied, a parameter associated with the WTRU using the first configuration information or the second configuration information. 2. The WTRU of claim 1 , wherein the interdependence RRC message reception time duration is preconfigured or is received from the DU RRC entity. 3. The WTRU of claim 1 or 2, wherein the determination that the second condition is satisfied comprises a determination that the first interdependency characteristic and the second interdependency characteristic indicate a same value. 4. The WTRU of claim 1 or 2, wherein the determination that the second condition is satisfied comprises a determination that the first interdependency characteristic and the second interdependency characteristic indicate that the first RRC message and the second RRC message are interdependent. 5. The WTRU of any of claims 1 to 4, wherein the processor is further configured to: send a first reconfiguration message to the DU RRC entity and a second reconfiguration message to the CU RRC entity, wherein the first reconfiguration message or the second reconfiguration message comprises an indication that the parameter is updated. 6. The WTRU of any of claims 1 to 4, wherein the parameter comprises a first parameter and a second parameter, and wherein the processor is further configured to: update, based on the determination that the first condition and the second condition are satisfied, the first parameter using the first configuration information and the second parameter using the second configuration information. 7. The WTRU of any of claims 1 to 4, wherein the processor is further configured to: determine that a third condition is satisfied, wherein the third condition is determined to be satisfied based on a WTRU speed satisfying a threshold; and update, based on the determination that the first condition, the second condition, and the third condition are satisfied, the parameter associated with the WTRU using the second configuration information. 8. The WTRU of any of claims 1 to 4, wherein the processor is further configured to: update, based on the determination that the first condition and the second condition are satisfied, the parameter associated with the WTRU using the first configuration information; and send a first reconfiguration message to the DU RRC entity and a second reconfiguration message to the CU RRC entity, wherein the first reconfiguration message comprises an indication that the parameter is updated based on the first configuration information, and the second reconfiguration message comprises an indication that the parameter is not updated based on the second configuration information. 9. The WTRU of any of claims 1 to 4, wherein the processor is further configured to: update, based on the determination that the first condition and the second condition are satisfied, the parameter associated with the WTRU using the second configuration information; and determine that one or more error conditions have occurred within a duration of time associated with an error checking time value, wherein the duration of time began at the time the parameter was updated using the second configuration information. 10. The WTRU of any of claims 1 to 4, wherein the processor is further configured to: receive a set of configuration information from the CU RRC entity; 

 determine that the update of the parameter associated with the WTRU using the first configuration information or the second configuration information results in a reconfiguration failure, wherein the update of the parameter is a first update; determine a third configuration information from the set of configuration information, wherein the third configuration information is compatible with the first configuration information; and perform a second update of the parameter associated with the WTRU using the first configuration or the third configuration. 11. A method comprising: receiving a first radio resource control (RRC) message from a distributed unit (DU) RRC entity, wherein the first RRC message indicates first configuration information and a first interdependency characteristic; in response to receiving the first RRC message, setting an interdependence RRC message timer based on an interdependence RRC message reception time duration; receiving a second RRC message from a control unit (CU) RRC entity, wherein the second RRC message indicates second configuration information and a second interdependency characteristic; determining that a first condition and a second condition are satisfied, wherein the first condition is determined to be satisfied based on the second RRC message being received before expiry of the interdependence RRC message timer, and wherein the second condition is determined to be satisfied based on the first interdependency characteristic and the second interdependency characteristic; and updating, based on determining that the first condition and the second condition are satisfied, a parameter associated with the WTRU using the first configuration information or the second configuration information. 12. The method of claim 11 , wherein the interdependence RRC message reception time duration is preconfigured or is received from the DU RRC entity. 13. The method of claim 11 or 12, wherein determining that the second condition is satisfied comprises a determination that the first interdependency characteristic and the second interdependency characteristic indicate a same value. 14. The method of claim 11 or 12, wherein determining that the second condition is satisfied comprises a determination that the first interdependency characteristic and the second interdependency characteristic indicate that the first RRC message and the second RRC message are interdependent. 15. The method of any of claims 11 to 14, wherein the method further comprises: sending a first reconfiguration message to the DU RRC entity and a second reconfiguration message to the CU RRC entity, wherein the first reconfiguration message or the second reconfiguration message comprises an indication that the parameter is updated. 16. The method of any of claims 11 to 14, wherein the parameter comprises a first parameter and a second parameter, and wherein the method further comprises: updating, based on the determination that the first condition and the second condition are satisfied, the first parameter using the first configuration information and the second parameter using the second configuration information. 17. The method of any of claims 11 to 14, wherein the method further comprises: determining that a third condition is satisfied, wherein the third condition is determined to be satisfied based on a WTRU speed satisfying a threshold; and updating, based on the determination that the first condition, the second condition, and the third condition are satisfied, the parameter associated with the WTRU using the second configuration information. 18. The method of any of claims 11 to 14, wherein the method further comprises: updating, based on the determination that the first condition and the second condition are satisfied, the parameter associated with the WTRU using the first configuration information; and sending a first reconfiguration message to the DU RRC entity and a second reconfiguration message to the CU RRC entity, wherein the first reconfiguration message comprises an indication that the parameter is updated based on the first configuration information, and the second reconfiguration message comprises an indication that the parameter is not updated based on the second configuration information. 19. The method of any of claims 11 to 14, wherein the method further comprises: updating, based on determining that the first condition and the second condition are satisfied, the parameter associated with the WTRU using the second configuration information; and determining that one or more error conditions have occurred within a duration of time associated with an error checking time value, wherein the duration of time began at the time the parameter was updated using the second configuration information. 20. The method of any of claims 11 to 14, wherein the method further comprises: receiving a fallback configuration from the DU RRC entity or the CU RRC entity; 

 determining that a failure condition for performing a recovery procedure is satisfied, wherein the failure condition indicates at least one of a reconfiguration failure, an integrity verification failure, or a handover failure; receiving a reconfiguration message from the DU RRC entity; and performing another update of the parameter based on the fallback configuration.
